Whirring then stopping—smegging typical. It’s probably out of the goop it uses to make food. I forgot to refill it once, and we ended up with a sandwich made of air—Lister ate it anyway, the slob. Check the goop tank behind the left hatch; it’s the one with the gauge that looks more confused than Rimmer during a surprise inspection. Speaking of surprises, I hope the Cat doesn’t wander in here looking for a loo—last time we were on that backwards Earth, he tried to un-dump in the bushes and nearly un-did himself out of existence.

